name: Vegetarian Garden Stir-Fry
author: Sami Link
summary: Perfect quick side dish for almost any meal. I recommend it with grilled chicken, peanut butter quinoa, rice, beans, avocado, etc. Can also be served as a vegetarian main.
ingredients: ½ cup dried fruit and nut mix, such as cranberries, almonds, and cashews
¼ cup bell pepper, thinly sliced
2 teaspoons cayenne pepper, or to taste
2 tablespoons shredded Cheddar cheese, or as desired
directions: Grease a large skillet with cooking spray and heat over medium-low heat
Add sugar snap peas, cherry tomatoes, fruit and nut mix, mushrooms, bell pepper, and chia seeds
Season with cayenne, garlic, and salt
Cook and stir about 2 minutes more
Stir in egg whites slowly, mixing until they are cooked through, but not crusty, 3 to 5 minutes
Transfer stir-fry to a large bowl and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese
